    <item>
      <title>OpenPOWERFoundation/a2o</title>
      <link>https://github.com/OpenPOWERFoundation/a2o</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The A2O core was a follow-on to A2I, written in Verilog, and supported a lower thread count than A2I, but higher performance per thread, using out-of-order execution (register renaming, reservation stations, completion buffer) and a store queue. It is now being updated for compliancy and integration into open projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;</description>
      
      <media:content url="https://opengraph.githubassets.com/e76c7826922e9e69edfcdd6f6b0d26419498f69be74ce377b0656b0d478c78ef/OpenPOWERFoundation/a2o" medium="image" />
      
